Uses of Package
nusri.fyp.demo.dto

Packages that use nusri.fyp.demo.dto
Package
Description
nusri.fyp.demo.controller
The nusri.fyp.demo.controller package contains the controllers responsible for handling HTTP requests in the demo application.
nusri.fyp.demo.dto
This package contains Data Transfer Object (DTO) classes used for transferring data between different layers of the application, such as between controllers and services.
nusri.fyp.demo.service
This package contains the service classes that handle the business logic of the application.
  • Classes in nusri.fyp.demo.dto used by nusri.fyp.demo.controller
    Class
    Description
    Alarm
    Represents an alert information that appears in a state machine or process, such as timeouts or execution order errors.
    JvmInfoDto
    DTO for returning JVM-level information such as memory usage, thread counts, and class loading details.
    PresetDto
    A DTO for preset data, used for returning simplified preset information at the interface or service layer.
    PresetNodeDto
    DTO corresponding to the PresetNode.
    ProgressBar
    Represents progress information for a node, including index, name, quota, parent node index list, and current progress percentage.
    StateMachineLogDto
    DTO for the state machine log, capturing details such as user, preset, start time, end time, and duration.
    StepStatsDto
    DTO for step statistics, including step name, average time, and standard deviation.
    SystemInfoDto
    DTO for returning system resource monitoring information, such as CPU usage, memory usage, and disk information.

    Description
